  "name": "Ovarian Cancer - CA-125 Tumor Marker Query (Elevated)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find ovarian cancer patients via elevated CA-125 (Cancer Antigen 125). CA-125 is the primary ovarian cancer tumor marker for diagnosis and surveillance. Normal range is <35 U/mL; values above 35 are clinically significant. Synthea generates CA-125 >100 U/mL for active ovarian cancer patients.",
  "prompt": "Find patients with elevated CA-125 (Cancer Antigen 125) lab results greater than 35 units per milliliter \u2014 the clinical threshold for ovarian cancer workup.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with high CA-125.",
    "broad": "Find patients with elevated Cancer Antigen 125 (CA-125) \u2014 values greater than 35 U/mL, the standard ovarian cancer screening and surveillance threshold.",
    "expert": "I need Observation resources with elevated CA-125. Use LOINC code 10334-1 (Cancer Ag 125 [Units/volume] in Serum or Plasma). Filter by value-quantity greater than 35 U/mL. Query: Observation?code=http://loinc.org|10334-1&value-quantity=gt35||U/mL"
  },
